    • Method Detail

      • hasNext

        public boolean hasNext()
        Returns, if there are more nodes in the tree. Actually, here the next node is determined. If the current node is a leaf, we have to go up, otherwise we always go down (depth first traversal).
        Specified by:
        hasNext in interface java.util.Iterator<javax.swing.tree.TreeNode>
        Returns:
        true, if there is a next node

      • remove

        public void remove()
        Removes the last returned tree node from this iterator. Note that the node is NOT removed from its tree, so no pointers in the node are changed. The consequence of this method call is that this iterator is not descending into the subtree defined by the last returned node, but is treating the node as leaf node.
        Specified by:
        remove in interface java.util.Iterator<javax.swing.tree.TreeNode>
